    <abstract>
      <t>Lisp-Nexagon is a geospatial intelligence network protocol designed to support physical-world applications such as transportation, public safety, and logistics. It combines the Locator/ID Separation Protocol (LISP) with the H3 spatial indexing system to enable distributed agents to report, aggregate, and disseminate geospatial state information.</t>
